<center><font face='arial'><br><br>





 <b>Ornate/Elemental Armour Quest</b><br><br>Here is a quick guide on how to transform your Ornate/Elemental pattern into the appropiate armour.<br><br>In the Plane of Tranquility, at pos705, neg1735 is a Dwarf called Bor Warhammer. (In the building to the right of the bank)<br><br><br><br>You need to give him 500 platinum (in platinum coins). Make sure you have room for a bag, as he will hand you a container and an emblem.<br><br>In this container, you need to combine the following (no fail, no trivial):<br><br><br> - Your Ornate/Elemental pattern<br> - The emblem<br> - 1-3 Ethereal Silk Swatches*<br><br><br>* 1 swatch for bracers, 2 swatches for boots, arms, cap or gloves, and 3 swatches for legs or robe.<br><br><b>Note:</b> The equivalent of elemental robe is a "Timeless Robe Pattern", which makes a "Timeless Silk Robe". It is made in exactly the same way.<br><br><br><br>To make Ethereal Silk Swatches combine the following in a planar sowing kit:<br><br> - Strand of Ether x 2<br> - Ethereal Curing Agent (Celestial Essence x2, Soda, Paela Sap)<br><br><br>The Curing Agent is brewed in a Tanaan Brew Barrel. Both the brewing and tailoring combine require 220 modified skill. (Celestial Essences are brewed from a celestial temper and a research component.)<br><br><br><br></center><b><u>Zone Information:</u></b><br><br>Zonelookup Failed!